<p class="govuk-body">
  The pattern helps users understand updates to something or actions taken so far. For example, a claim history.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="when-to-use">When to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Use the timeline pattern when you need to show a brief list of entries in chronological order. For example, the stages involved in asking for and getting a tax repayment.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="when-to-use">When not to use</h2>
<p class="govuk-body"> Do not use the timeline pattern if you need to let users know where they are in a journey. In this case, consider another approach </p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="how-it-works">How it works</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Each item in the timeline should have:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet" role="list">
<li> a title</li>
<li>the date and, or time</li>
<li>a description (optional)</li>
</ul>

